## 整合 httpd svn 与 redmine 的用户登陆
### 分析 redmine 表结构
用 paadmin,可以看到 redmine 数据库有这样一个 users 表
```sql
CREATE TABLE users
(
  id serial NOT NULL,
  login character varying(255) NOT NULL DEFAULT ''::character varying,
  hashed_password character varying(40) NOT NULL DEFAULT ''::character varying,
  firstname character varying(30) NOT NULL DEFAULT ''::character varying,
  lastname character varying(30) NOT NULL DEFAULT ''::character varying,
  mail character varying(60) NOT NULL DEFAULT ''::character varying,
  admin boolean NOT NULL DEFAULT false,
  status integer NOT NULL DEFAULT 1,
  last_login_on timestamp without time zone,
  language character varying(5) DEFAULT ''::character varying,
  auth_source_id integer,
  created_on timestamp without time zone,
  updated_on timestamp without time zone,
  type character varying(255),
  identity_url character varying(255),
  mail_notification character varying(255) NOT NULL DEFAULT ''::character varying,
  salt character varying(64),
  CONSTRAINT users_pkey PRIMARY KEY (id )
)
```

关注以下几个字段就 ok 了
```sql
CREATE TABLE users
(
  id serial NOT NULL,
  login character varying(255) NOT NULL DEFAULT ''::character varying,
  hashed_password character varying(40) NOT NULL DEFAULT ''::character varying,
  status integer NOT NULL DEFAULT 1,
  type character varying(255),
)
```
- login 登陆用户名
- hashed_password 是以 SHA1 加密过的密码 
- status = 1 代表状态正常 
- type = User 時表示为用户(若 type = Group 表示为群组)
### 增加 mod_auth_pgsql2 SHA1 加密功能

网上搜到 redmine 密码用的是 sha1 加密

悲剧,mod_auth_pgsql2 并不支持 SHA1 加密..

于是我辛苦的修改了 mod_auth_pgsql.c,让  mod_auth_pgsql2 支持 sha1 加密:

我利用的 ssh 带的加密,需要安装有 ssh-dev
```bash
sudo yum install openssl-devel
```
注意加入头
```c
#include <openssl/sha.h>
```
主要增加了函数
```c
static char *auth_pg_sha1(char *pw) {

    int i = 0;
    unsigned char temp![pic](SHA_DIGEST_LENGTH);
    char buf![pic](SHA_DIGEST_LENGTH*2);


    memset(buf, 0x0, SHA_DIGEST_LENGTH*2);
    memset(temp, 0x0, SHA_DIGEST_LENGTH);

    SHA1(pw, strlen(pw), temp);

    for (i=0; i < SHA_DIGEST_LENGTH; i++) {
        sprintf((char*)&(buf![pic](i*2)), "%02x", temp![pic](i));
    }

    return buf;
}
```

